Virginia Tech, founded in 1872, dominates life in Blacksburg with a $900 million budget.
The campus, known for its Electronic Village, became the site of the deadliest school shooting in US history.
The gunman killed 32 people before taking his own life.
The FBI ruled out terrorism as the motive.
President Bush attended a memorial service, calling it a "day of sadness" for the nation.
Classes were canceled for the week as the community mourned the tragic event.
The Virginia Tech community and the nation grieved the loss of innocent lives.
